# Rule: SPEC.md

`SPEC.md` is a **component index**, not a monolithic product spec.
It grows one row per component, **in the same PR that ships the
component**. A row whose component has not shipped yet is forbidden;
the doc must never speculate.

A row has these columns, in this order:

| Column | Source |
|---|---|
| Component | One short noun phrase (`Supervisor`, `Wire protocol`, `CLI`, …). |
| Package(s) | `packages/<name>` paths that implement it. |
| ADR(s) | One or more `docs/adr/NNNN-<slug>.md` ids. Listed in numeric order. |
| Rule(s) | `.agents/rules/<name>.md.rule` ids that govern the component's `.md` files (excluding the SPEC rule itself). |
| Skill(s) | `.agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` ids that touch the component (if any). |
| Memory facts | `.agents/memory/facts/*.md` paths the component relies on (if any). |

The doc must:

- contain only the index table and a one‑paragraph mission link
  back to `AGENTS.md` and `docs/adr/README.md`;
- not contain a glossary, an FR/NFR list, persona write‑ups, or
  architecture prose — those live in the cited ADRs and memory
  entries;
- stay under ~80 lines.

A new row is added by the PR that introduces the first ADR for
the component; removing a row requires an ADR that explicitly
retires the component.

## Template

```markdown
# SPEC.md — Hookorama component index

> Read AGENTS.md and docs/adr/README.md before extending this
> document. Rows are added by the PR that introduces the component;
> pre‑written rows are forbidden.

| Component | Package(s) | ADR(s) | Rule(s) | Skill(s) | Memory facts |
|-----------|-----------|--------|---------|----------|--------------|
| … | … | … | … | … | … |
```